## Nodemon
## Express.js

``` const express = require('express');
const app = express();

app.get('/annu', (req, res) => {
    res.status(200).send({ userName: "Annu" });
})

const slash = (req,res) => {
    res.send("Hello From Function");
}; 
```

const express = require("express"); // Imported the express module from the node_modules folder.
const app = express(); // Express passes a function definition (export = e) which we need to call before moving ahead and being able to use express.

app.listen(5000);
// We launched our local server at port 5000 where express will be listening to the requests: CRUD -> POST, GET, PUT, DELETE Operation





